            <p>Pets are loving members of families whom it is difficult to imagine leaving behind for a journey. Now, with the help of the Allegiant Airlines pet carrier policy, travellers no longer need to do that. Travellers no longer have to make arrangements at shelters or with trusted friends or family members but can easily bring their companions along. Travellers will find it very easy to navigate the trip with the help of this article outlining important facts about the policy.</p>
            <p>Allegiant Air is the major airline for the travel goals and if you are thinking to consider this airline for the travel purpose with your pet then you must know about the Allegiant Pet Carrier Dimensions. Pet carrier dimensions are the most important aspect for the flyers because if they not follow the pet carrier dimensions then they need to pay higher cost to travel with pet or pet carrier may also rejected by the airline. Pet carrier dimensions as per the pet policy of the airline must not exceed than 9”H x 16”W x 19”D.</p>

            <h2>Allegiant Airlines – The Affordable Choice</h2>
            <p>Allegiant Airlines is a popular airport that follows a low-cost carrier model well complemented with multiple operating bases spread all over the United States of America. They help the airline in carrying out its mundane day-to-day business which includes details such as ensuring compliance with Allegiant pet policy weight limit.</p>
            <p>The operating bases are the Des Moines International Airport which is located in the city of Des Moines in Iowa state, the Bishop International Airport located in the city of Flint and the Grand Rapids Gerard R. Ford International Airport which is located in the Cascade Township near the Grand Rapids city of the Michigan State, and the Orlando Sanford International Airport located in the Sanford city near Orlando city in Florida state.</p>
            <p>This provides travellers more accessibility to its customers who avail its services to various corners of the country allowing them to seek assistance while boarding the flights with their pets. While direct help might not be available, travellers can learn more about guidelines and adhere to them to ensure a comfortable journey for their fellow travellers and themselves.</p>

            <h2>Strictness and Flexibility</h2>
            <p>The most common question that all travellers using Allegiant Airlines for their journeys have is <b>how strict is Allegiant with pet carriers</b>. For their travel websites. Travellers will find that the airlines is a perfect mix of rigidity and flexibility allowing travellers adjustments for their comfort but drawing a line where it comes to a matter of safety and the comfort of fellow travellers.</p>
            <p>The number one rule that the airlines insist upon for the collective safety of all travellers is that the pets are always kept within carriers and the carrier is exclusively handled by the traveller. The pets must be non-violent, refrain from causing any disruption in others’ enjoyment of the trip, clean and hygienic to prevent any odour from emanating from them.</p>
            <p>The airlines also insist that all travellers must keep their pets do not sit in the exit row or the dividing region between different compartments of the flight as well as an aisle seat on an aircraft from the Boeing company. In case a passenger is assigned an aisle seat at the time of reservation, they shall be reassigned another seat upon boarding.</p>

            <h2>For the Comforts of the Furred Ones</h2>
            <p>Travellers must make sure that their pets are not in distress within their carriers and the airlines have strict rules regarding <b>Allegiant pet carrier dimensions</b>. The maximum limit has been set at eight inches in height, fourteen inches in width and eighteen inches in length carrying only two pets at the most with enough space for the comfort of the inhabitant.</p>
            <p>A soft-sided carrier is also strongly recommended as well as any medication that any traveller might wish to administer to their pet. All travellers must only carry a single carrier which will be counted among the two carry-on articles that every traveller is allowed to carry given that Allegiant Airlines will not allow any pet carriers in the cargo.</p>
            <p>Travellers should note that the airlines will only allow domestic cats and dogs above the age of eight weeks on board the flight. Travellers need not carry a health certificate for their animal for the airlines but they will need to comply with Transportation Security Administration guidelines to bring them with themselves.</p>

            <h2>What All Travellers on Allegiant Airlines Need to Know?</h2>
            <p>An important point that all travellers opting for <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/allegiant-airlines.aspx"><b>Allegiant Airlines</b></a> should know is that travellers must pay a fee of fifty dollars for their carriers and check in with an agent of the airlines at the nearest ticket counter an hour prior to boarding to ensure that they are in compliance. Travellers should also note that they will be unable to bring animals outside of the forty-eight contiguous states of the United States of America.</p>
            <p>Passengers at the airlines should remember that they need to be in compliance with their guidelines or they or their pet might not be allowed to board the flight or other flights of the airlines any further. The airline has not set any <b>Allegiant pet policy weight limit</b> and only requires that the comfort of the pet is ensured with adequate area for the animal to move about within the carrier which needs to be kept beneath the seat. Every traveller paying for a ticket is allowed a single pet carrier.</p>

